Package: comments
Title: Add comments to your R data frames as you modify them to document the reasons for your changes
Version: 0.0.3
Authors@R: person("Mark", "Smith", email = "msmith77@nd.edu", role = c("aut", "cre"))
Description: This package allows you to add an attribute to your R objects that can be used to store comments.
    It provides a set of functions to list, add, and delete comments. It can also be used with the dplyr package.
Depends: R (>= 3.4.0)
License: MIT + file LICENSE
Encoding: UTF-8
LazyData: true
RoxygenNote: 6.1.1.9000
Imports:
    githubinstall,
    dplyr
Suggests:
    knitr,
    rmarkdown,
    covr,
    testthat
URL: https://github.com/mandpd/comments
BugReports: https://github.com/mandpd/comments/issues
